reviewText:
I love looking at the characters through the actor's eyes.  The respect and depth of their roles makes this so much than a zombie series.
These earlier years are new to me as I've only gotten into The WalkingDead in season 5.  I am totally addicted!
Love "The Walking Dead" & I adore any opportunity to hear the cast, creator, writers, producers, etc. discuss the ins & outs of the process of creating the show!
Cast are great!! I can do without the sarcastic/overly dramatic host.
Ya gotta live the walking dead... what else can I say?
I didn't realize I had missed a Paley Center showing with the Walking Dead Cast...which happens to be my favorite show. Thanks for providing this on DVD..I love it!
Fun interview show. It's a couple years old but still fun to watch.  This is from their first season. Several of the cast are gone

great to see these actors out of character....too bad many of them have been executed from the show.... the director and writer are  very gratuitous with their foul language , be prepared for your ears!  I think that the actors studio series may do a better job....no one has explained about the English/Australian actors involved in this series....
Love all the cast Love this show
It was from Season 3.  Interesting looking back!
This was better than the first, the actors had more time to answer questions from the audience and online.

Oh look.. it's the Frank Darabonte show.
Look I've defended the guy from a creative perspective but now that I've seen this display of attention grabbing hubris, I have a better picture of what it must have been like for cast and crew behind the scenes. Frank is all about Frank, and the rest of the cast really had no reason to even show up to this event. Irritating.
Great seeing all the Stars relaxed.  They really enjoy the show!!
It was okay. Later ones with Chris Hardwick are so much better!
Can't ever get enough of TWD. The cast is a smart and funny group.
I love these Paleyfest specials. It's great to see the actors, producers writers and all together talking about the show and giving insights to certain scenes or episodes.
I would of like to hear more from the actors instead of the producers.
